= MIKBUG/SmithBug =

* MIKBUG was a monitor program for the 6800
* [http://www.retrotechnology.com/restore/smithbug.html SmithBug] is a variant of MIKBUG which uses the VDU/ACIA port

= MIKBUG Commands =

Smithbug has the following case-sensitive commands.

* Memory opertations
** V - View Memory - space for next page, enter to exit
** E - Change Memory - prompts for - address, enter 2 digits or enter to exit
** M - Move Memory - prompts for From Start, From End, To addresses
** I - Fill Memory
** F - Find - prompts for Start, End, value to search for
* Code development
** D - Disassemble Code
** & - S1 Load Program
** G - Go to Program
** J - Jump to Target Program
** R - Print Registers
* Execution
** T - Trace Program
** K - Continue after break
** 1 - Breakpoint ONE
** 2 - Breakpoint TWO
* Printer control
** H - Printer On
* Misc
** @ - ASCII Conversion
** Q - Hardware Location
** O - Echo On
** N - Echo Off

=	Memory Map (32KB SRAM or less cases) =

* 0x0000-0x7FFF - 32KB Internal SRAM (can work with as little as 3.5KB SRAM)
**  0x7F00-0x7FFF - RAM used by MIKBUG (256 bytes)
* 0xC000-0xFFFF - 4 KB ROM (repeats 4x)
** 0xC8D5 - Last address (plus reset vector at 0xFFFE,0xFFFF)
* 0x8000-0x80FF - I/O space (512 bytes)
** 0x8018-0x8019 - VDU/UART (6850 Interface)
** 0x8028-0x8029 - UART/VDU (6850 Interface)
* 0xFFFE-0xFFFF - Reset vector (ROM)

=	Memory Map (60KB SRAM case) =

Can be used with less SRAM, but there needs to be a scratchpad SRAM from 0xEF00-0xEFFF.

* 0x0000-0x7FFF - 32KB Internal or External SRAM
* 0x8000-0xBFFF - 16Kb SRAM bank (64 banks)
* 0xC000-0xEFFF - 12KB Internal SRAM
**  0xEF00-0xEFFF - RAM used by MIKBUG (256 bytes)
* 0xF000-0xFFFF - 4 KB ROM (carve out for I/O space)
** 0xF8D3 - Last address (plus reset vector at 0xFFFE,0xFFFF)
* 0xFC00-0xFDFF - I/O space (512 bytes)
** 0xFC18-0xFC19 - VDU/UART (6850 Interface)
** 0xFC28-0xFC29 - UART/VDU (6850 Interface)
** 0xFC30 - Bank Select register (r/w)
* 0xFFFE-0xFFFF - Reset vector (ROM)

